<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4414] unaryMinus fails for Short and Byte</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4414</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Short&lt;/span&gt; s = 1
println(-s)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;fails with the following exception:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;groovy.lang.MissingMethodException: No signature of method: java.lang.Short.negative() is applicable for argument types: () values: []&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens because &lt;tt&gt;org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper#unaryMinus&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t negate &lt;tt&gt;Short&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;Byte&lt;/tt&gt; directly, but falls through to a call to non-existent function &lt;tt&gt;negative&lt;/tt&gt; on those objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please find attached a patch for a test case (&lt;tt&gt;InvokerHelperTest&lt;/tt&gt;), and a patch for a proposed fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patches are done with git, hope this is OK. If it isn&apos;t, please let me know for future reference.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
